  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UNDSS Security Support for Humanitarian Operations to 7.5 Magnitude Earthquake affected areas in Southern Highlands and Hela Province</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide dedicated security support for the expanded life-saving humanitarian operations in the Highlands of PNG following the earthquake. UNDP/DSS will use CERF funds to undertake four security risk assessments, conduct 100 security missions, provide 20 biweekly security briefings, issue 10 biweekly analytical reports and advisories and 100 daily situational reports. All humanitarian partners will benefit from this project, which will be implemented within four months.</narrative>
  </description>
